article.headline: IUPUI 74, Texas Southern 55
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Alex Young hit five 3-point shots, Sean Esposito added four from long range and Indiana University-Purdue University Indianapolis broke open a close game with a big second half for a 74-55 victory over Texas Southern on Saturday night. Young finished with 30 points and Esposito 12 points for the Jaguars (2-4). Lyonell Gaines and Christian Siakam each had 10 rebounds. IUPUI converted 7 of 13 3-point shots in the second half to spark a 46-27 run after the teams were deadlocked at 28 at halftime. IUPUI also scored 15 second-chance points, nearly double that of the Tigers (1-4). Texas Southern suffered a cold-shooting night, hitting just 34.4 percent of its field-goal attempts and just 11.1 on its 3-point tries. Omar Strong came off the bench to score 12 points for Texas Southern.
